a few of my Los Angeles favorites 🫶 

• @gjustaflowershop - the prettiest corner shop florist - stunning flowers & a darling lil photo op ;) 
• @gjustagrocer - just adjacent you’ll find their grocery market. Got to be one of the prettiest I’ve seen! Makes me want to fill a basket of unique foods for a friend. You won’t want to leave empty handed. 
• @greatwhite - hands down my favorite breakfast burrito to date. The ambiance also cannot be beat! (PS download their app for a free breakfast burrito 😏) 
• Santa Monica Farmer’s market - Wed & Sat 8am-1pm just so dang charming

My kind of morning! 🌞☕️🥐🎲 if you’re looking to have your morning made in Joshua tree- you’ve got to pop into the sweet @lunasourdough where all your sourdough dreams come true. Do not leave without the cinnamon rolls! Emphasis on plural!! The sweet spot for me will always be something sweet AND savory! 
Make this your first stop as fresh goods are quick to leave the shelves and i promise you don’t want to miss out. Early bird gets the worm 🥐 
Follow that with @masomenosbar where you can really melt into those mornings hours with a warm drink, an array of little games ( i eat this up) & a patio full of morning sunlight & sometimes yoga! The kind of place that leaves you saying “ i wanna stay!!”

Mmm just telling y’all bout it brings the good feels :)

the latest of country living 🌾
1. head over heels for wood paneled walls. So cozy while everything pops against it! 
2. It’s being tempted to pull over at every dang pasture of sweet animals. It’s a dream when every road home looks like like this! 
3. The pure giddiness of being back on the water. Sun-kissed, tipsy & wake surfing! It could not have been more missed. 
4.  Our first pool day of the year with our sweet summer weather. Once it starts- it’s daily!! 
5. Dates in the country - taking the top of the Jeep for a sunset cruise to the creek. It’s the simplest but sweetest. 
6. Hikes with my favorite sidekick & mama. Giddy that there will never not be more to explore. Even in your hometown!! 
7. Collecting all sorts of dinner & home good treasures with all my garage sales & finally setting the table for family dinner with them. Precious. 
8. Savoring in spring’s extra hours with a little something on ice :) 
9. Shared joys over new hobbies 🤗
10. The peace this view gives me daily! ♡

Happy National pollinators week 🐝 celebrating our pollinators with @manukahealthusa & a little daily dose of nature’s nectar! 🍯 Raw Mãnuka honey has so many beautiful benefits from Immune health, skin care, & gut health.- the list goes on. While none of these lovely benefits exist without the help of our bee’s & pollinators who sustain our stunning vast eco system! A few ways to support our pollinators this week include:

cheers to 2024 🌸
Ahhh these years just keep going faster and faster, just as they warned us. Seasons feel so short, I feel like I’m constantly grasping to hold onto them or revel in them while they’re here & the over-sharer in me has surely been slacking! I’ve found, as the years keep counting, that life & time is sooo far from linear. It’s almost not at all what I imagined it would be. It’s abundant and complicated and messy & it seems the more you learn, the less you truly know in this wild life. Always leads me to more & more questions! The “new” in new year always gives me quick butterflies. That instinct of optimism for the many, many chances we have to begin again! To be inspired! To try something new! To reflect! To take catalog of all that is GOOD! Cheers for what’s to come :)
